## grep 

[0-9a-f][0-9a-f] : two hex bit

	peter@bull:~$ grep [0-9a-f][0-9a-f] test 
	12
	aa
	1a
	peter@bull:~$ cat test 
	12
	1
	aa
	1a

	peter@bull:~$ 

find a word, case ignored

	peter@bull:~$ grep -i  '\<hello\>'  dd
	hello
	hello my love
	Hello

## pipe the output to vim

then I can do some highliting automatically

and anything I want later manually

	peter@bull:~$ cat v.vim 
	i  hello

	peter@bull:~$ vim -s v.vim newfile
	peter@bull:~$ cat newfile 
	  hello


	peter@bull:~$ 

